    • PantryZone

      public PantryZone(String name, int userId, int minTemp, int maxTemp, int minHum, int maxHum, int minBright, int maxBright)
      Constructor to create a new PantryZone before it is inserted into the database.
      Parameters:
      name - name of the zone (e.g. fridge, pantry, fruitBowl, ...),
      userId - id of the user that owns the zone
      minTemp - if the recorded temperature in that zone goes under this value, it will send a notification to the user
      maxTemp - if the recorded temperature in that zone goes over this value, it will send a notification to the user
      minHum - if the recorded humidity in that zone goes under this value, it will send a notification to the user
      maxHum - if the recorded humidity in that zone goes over this value, it will send a notification to the user
      minBright - if the recorded brightness in that zone goes under this value, it will send a notification to the user
      maxBright - if the recorded brightness in that zone goes over this value, it will send a notification to the user

    • PantryZone

      public PantryZone(int id, String name, int minTemp, int maxTemp, int minHum, int maxHum, int minBright, int maxBright)
      Constructor used when getting a pantryZone from the database with id included.
      Parameters:
      id - ties the pantryZone to the DB
      name - name of the zone (e.g. fridge, pantry, fruitBowl, ...)
      minTemp - if the recorded temperature in that zone goes under this value, it will send a notification to the user
      maxTemp - if the recorded temperature in that zone goes over this value, it will send a notification to the user
      minHum - if the recorded humidity in that zone goes under this value, it will send a notification to the user
      maxHum - if the recorded humidity in that zone goes over this value, it will send a notification to the user
      minBright - if the recorded brightness in that zone goes under this value, it will send a notification to the user
      maxBright - if the recorded brightness in that zone goes over this value, it will send a notification to the user
